# Chosen Development Model
For developing our project, the method we chose is the agile development method. Given that this is the first project we are working on as a team, we think that our project will develop and evolve throughout creation. As such, we think that a model appropriate for our project is one that allows us to make changes along the way as we come up with new and improved ideas of features we are working on implementing.

# User Requirements
a. Stakeholders: 
- End-users: Citizens of Albania interested in discarding items they no longer use, or citizens that are interested in buying second-hand goods with decent quality for reasonable prices.
- Developers: The project team members who will work on making the marketplace system a reality.
b. User Stories
- As a user/buyer, I want to be able to browse through commodities other people are putting up for sale. I want to have filtering options such as keywords, price-sorting, or proximity sorting to see what items are realistic for me to seek out.
- As a user/buyer, I want to be able to message sellers to ask for more information or pictures of the commodity they are offering. 
- As a user/seller, I want to add pictures and descriptions of the items I am putting up for sale.
- As a user/seller, I want to add/update/delete items for sale. I want to add multiple pictures and descriptions. If an item is sold, I want to be able to mark it as such.
- As both a buyer and a seller, I want a two-way review system that records transaction experiences, so users can assess whether the other party is trustworthy or potentially fraudulent. 
- For similar purposes, I want a report function to escalate improper behaviour to customer care agents for reviewing.
- As a user/buyer I want to be able to favorite items that I might be interested in. I want to be able to view them again in a wishlist so they're easily accessible. 
- As a user/ buyer I want to be able to negotiate with sellers in order to make items more affordable.
- As a user I want to receive notifications in order to respond quickly to messages from other users.
- As a user I want to be able to view other users' profiles in order to see how trustworthy they are before interacting with them.  
- As a user/buyer I want to be able to view the location of an item in order to see if they are close enough for me to want to purchase.
- As a user I want to be able to view past interactions so I can keep track of my activity.

# Functional Requirements
a. User authentication: The system should allow users to register and create an account.
Acceptance criteria:
A person uses ID number to create an account. 
They are prompted to create an account using email and by setting a password.
Credentials are verified.
The registered user is redirected to the home page.
b. User log in: System should allow users to log in and out of their accounts.
Acceptance criteria:
The user enters their email and password to log in.
Credentials are verified by the system.
If invalid credentials are submitted, “Invalid credentials” message is displayed on screen prompting the user to try again.
c. Home page browsing: The system should provide users with a way to seek out items within feasible real life (monetary or location) constraints.
Acceptance criteria:
After successful log in, users are redirected to the software’s home page displaying items for sale.
Search functionality that users type words into to find items with titles fully or partially matching with what the user wrote.
d. Filtering System: System should allow users to filter items based on specific criteria.
Acceptance criteria:
Filter buttons that users can toggle to check items within a specific price range or within a specified radius. 
Results will be updated based on the filters set.
Search options should be stackable allowing for filtering within filtering.
e. Item creation/edit/deletion: Registered users can upload items for sale by writing a title, uploading picture(s), writing a short description, and putting a base asking price. After uploading the item, they can change information or delete it fully.
Acceptance criteria:
User goes to create an item button.
He fills in the form with the appropriate information and confirms creation.
If needed, user can make changes to item created. *Edited information is logged in cases where change is committed for fraudulent purposes*
If user changes his mind, he can delete the item poster entirely. 
f. Item viewing: System should allow users to view detailed information about the listed items.
Acceptance criteria:
User clicks on the item they want to view.
The item page displays all information about the item such as price, condition, description, seller information.
g. Item status: System should allow sellers to update the status of the items.
Acceptance criteria:
Sellers can mark items as sold.
The sold items are clearly marked and not shown on search pages only in the sellers profile or wishlist.
h. Multiple images uploads: System allows sellers to upload multiple images for the items they're listing.
Acceptance criteria:
Users can upload more than one photo.
All images are displayed in the detailed item viewing page.
i. Rating system: After a transaction has been completed, seller and buyer can give a rating (out of 5) to each other based on how smooth the interaction and transaction went.
Acceptance criteria:
Both parties confirm the transaction happened.
Review feature is unlocked.
Users rate each other and have the option to add justification or information on their review.
j. Report system: Users can report fraudulent or improper behaviour.
Acceptance criteria:
Users visit other users’ profiles.
From the profile, they can submit a report on the user.
Option to add screenshots and elaborate text description. 
k. Messaging system: Users and sellers can communicate with each other in order to ask for extra information.
Acceptance criteria:
Users can open a chat from an item listing.
Messages can be sent and received between users and sellers.
Chat history is stored and accessible.
l. Wishlist and favorites: System allows users to add items to wishlist for later viewing.
Acceptance criteria:
Users are able to mark items as favorites.
Wishlist appears in the users profile.
Users are able to remove items off of their wishlist.
m. User Profile: Allows users to manage their information.
Acceptance criteria:
Users are able to view, edit, add and delete their information.
Can view past purchases, wishlist etc.
n. Location Services: System provides location based features for more relevant searches.
Acceptance criteria:
Users can allow access to location.
Items display approximate distance from user.
o. Category system: Items are put into categories for easier search.
Acceptance criteria:
Sellers can select a category when listing an item.
Users can select categories when searching for items.
Items are displayed under their categories.
p. Condition specification: Sellers should be able to specify the condition of the items they are listing.
Conditions of items are displayed on the listings.
Users can select the condition based on what they are looking for.
Sellers can place the condition.
q. History Tracking system: System should keep track of negotiations of prices.
Acceptance criteria:
All offers and counteroffers are stored.
Users can view the final price.
r. Blocking System: Users can block other users.
Acceptance criteria:
Users are able to block other users.
They cant see blocked users or their listings.
Users are able to unblock users if they decide to.
s. Password reset: System should allow users to reset their passwords in case of them forgetting.
Acceptance criteria:
Users are able to request a password reset.
The reset link is sent on the users email.
t. Admin page: A page for the admins to have access to tools for managing the system.
Acceptance criteria:
Reports submitted by users can be viewed. 
Banning or suspension of users.
Removing listings if they don't follow regulations.
u. Listing date display: System should show when items are posted.
Acceptance criteria: 
Every item shows the date that it was posted.
Users can see how recent an item listing is.
v. Notifications: System should allow users to view notifications.
Acceptance criteria:
Users have access to a notification section.
Here they are able to view when an item is sold, when a message is sent etc.

