# Application Specifications
a. Architecture
The system will consist of three parts: the frontend, backend, and the database. Through the frontend interfaces users will send requests to the backend, which in turn, will pull the data from the database to complete the request.
b. Database Model
An Entity Relationship Diagram will be used. The database will include entities such as users, items, categories, messages, reviews, wishlist, and report. Entities such as users, items and categories will have unique IDs to make sure they can be separately identified. Other entities will consist of information (the primary keys) from other entities. For example, messages will have sender's ID and receiver's ID, alongside message content. Wishlist will have user ID and item ID. All entities mentioned will also contain additional attributes to be as clear as possible.
c. Technologies Used
For the development of our software system backend we will use Python's Django framework. To handle the database system we will use PostgreSQL. As for our frontend development, we will use Django templates that use HTML, CSS and JavaScript.
d. User Interface Design
Users begin on a registration and login page. After logging in, the main page displays recently listed items. The interface will be minimalistic as to not confuse non tech-savvy users. There will be a button to access your own profile, alongside buttons to add an item for sale. There will also be buttons for searching as well as clickable, paginated tabs for items on the landing page.
e. Security Measures
For the safety of our users, passwords will be hashed and their IDs will be encrypted to make sure that no data leak or theft causes harm to the system users.
